CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 12, 1941, pg. 12 reads: "Courier Cameras Click As Colorful Eastern Open Unfolds On South Park's Beautiful Golf Course - Notables and settings at South Park during the colorful Eastern Open Golf Association's amateur tournament staged here Saturday and Sunday under the direction of the local Yorkshire Golf Club...Heavyweight champion Joe Louis, after a beautiful drive down the fairways...Harris and staff photographers."
TitMainTitle: Boxer Joe Louis putting golf ball at South Park golf club for Eastern Open Golf Association amateur tournament
